---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Faltoobot — WhatsApp-first AI with terminal chat">
  <div class="page-shell">
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="hero__backdrop" aria-hidden="true">
        <div class="hero__terminal">
          <p>$ uv tool install faltoobot</p>
          <p>$ faltoobot configure</p>
          <p>$ faltoobot auth</p>
          <p>$ faltoobot install</p>
          <p>$ faltoochat "draft a release note"</p>
        </div>
        <div class="hero__messages">
          <p>WhatsApp → Explain MCP in 5 bullets</p>
          <p>Faltoobot → concise, useful, ready to send</p>
          <p>Terminal → queue prompts, review diffs, fix code</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero__overlay"></div>
      <Header />
      <div class="hero__content">
        <p class="hero__brand">Faltoobot</p>
        <h1>WhatsApp-first AI, with a terminal chat built for real work.</h1>
        <p class="hero__lede">
          Run one assistant on its own WhatsApp account, or use the same model
          locally with <code>faltoochat</code> for coding, review, and everyday work.
        </p>
        <div class="hero__actions">
          <a class="button button--primary" href="#install">Install with uv</a>
          <a class="button button--secondary" href="/docs/guide/">Read the guide</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <main>
      <section class="section section--install" id="install">
        <div class="section__intro">
          <p class="section__eyebrow">Install</p>
          <h2>Install it in one command.</h2>
          <p>
            Start with the CLI install, then pair the WhatsApp account once.
            After that, you can run the bot in the background or open the local terminal chat.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="install-command" aria-label="Install command">
          <span>$</span>
          <code>uv tool install faltoobot</code>
        </div>
        <p class="section__note">
          For faster project search in <code>faltoochat</code>, also install <code>ripgrep</code>.
        </p>
        <div class="command-list">
          <div>
            <h3>Then configure it</h3>
            <pre><code>faltoobot configure</code></pre>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>Pair the WhatsApp account</h3>
            <pre><code>faltoobot auth</code></pre>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>Run in the background</h3>
            <pre><code>faltoobot install</code></pre>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section section--use">
        <div class="section__intro">
          <p class="section__eyebrow">Use it your way</p>
          <h2>One assistant, two surfaces.</h2>
          <p>
            Keep Faltoobot on WhatsApp for quick requests, and use <code>faltoochat</code>
            when you want a local workspace with tools, images, queued prompts, and review mode.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="split-copy">
          <div>
            <h3>On WhatsApp</h3>
            <p>
              Private replies, image support, and simple slash commands like <code>/help</code>
              and <code>/reset</code>.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>In the terminal</h3>
            <p>
              Use <code>faltoochat</code> for coding workflows, session history, local skills,
              and git-aware review tabs.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section section--docs">
        <div class="section__intro">
          <p class="section__eyebrow">Documentation</p>
          <h2>Need the full setup guide?</h2>
          <p>
            Start with the guide for commands, config, allowlists, file layout, and development notes.
          </p>
        </div>
        <a class="docs-link" href="/docs/guide/">Open the Faltoobot guide</a>
      </section>
    </main>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
